  <!-- Content -->
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-600 mb-4">Common Signs of Dehydration</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Dehydration happens when your body loses more fluid than it takes in. Recognizing early warning signs can help prevent fatigue, headaches, and health issues.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-600 mt-8 mb-2">Early Symptoms</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <li>Dry mouth or cracked lips</li>
      <li>Dark yellow urine</li>
      <li>Low energy or fatigue</li>
      <li>Dizziness or lightheadedness</li>
      <li>Increased thirst</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-600 mt-8 mb-2">Advanced Signs</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <li>Rapid heartbeat</li>
      <li>Confusion or irritability</li>
      <li>Very dry skin</li>
      <li>No urine for over 8 hours</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mt-6 text-gray-700">
      Use our  
      <a href="../hydration.html" class="text-emerald-600 font-medium hover:underline">
        Hydration Calculator
      </a>  
      to estimate how much water your body needs.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-6">*Seek medical attention if symptoms worsen or persist.</p>
  </main>

